headline: Coca-Cola Consolidated: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) — Coca-Cola Consolidated, Inc. COKE) on Wednesday reported net income of $142.3 million in its third quarter. On a per-share basis, the Charlotte, North Carolina-based company said it had profit of $1.64.

headline: How To Boost The Yield On Coca-Cola Stock Using Options
summary: Coca-Cola is a resilient, dividend-paying consumer staples giant with a global footprint and strong brand loyalty.  There's a reason why Coca-Cola stock has been a famous long-term investment by Warren Buffett, and it has reaped billions in capital gains and dividends.  Income investors may be interested in further enhancing the attractive dividend yield through the use of covered calls.

headline: In Search of Warren Buffett’s Fund Heirs
summary: FUNDS  It’s hard to imagine anyone taking Warren Buffett’s place. But at 95, the investing legend is retiring as CEO of Berkshire Hathaway at year end. And with the once-sleepy textile company he acquired in 1965 now a trillion-dollar conglomerate, it will be difficult for even the savviest successor to maneuver such a behemoth to trounce the market like Buffett once did.
